<item>
            <title>[CXF-3631] WADL Generator ignores @PathParams mapped on class fields</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-3631</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have a request scoped resource via a RequestScopeResourceFactory and &amp;lt;aop:scoped-proxy /&amp;gt; as described on &lt;a href=&quot;http://cxf.apache.org/docs/jaxrs-services-configuration.html#JAXRSServicesConfiguration-Lifecyclemanagement&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://cxf.apache.org/docs/jaxrs-services-configuration.html#JAXRSServicesConfiguration-Lifecyclemanagement&lt;/a&gt; to be able to inject @PathParams on class fields. This works as expected however the mapped parameters do not show up in the auto-generated WADL. After a quick look in the source code of org.apache.cxf.jaxrs.model.wadl.WADLGenerator it seems it is only looking for method-level parameters.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
